01:36:09,760 --> 01:36:12,120
It's like this automated drone sort of thing.

1415
01:36:12,120 --> 01:36:13,160
Automated drone, yeah.

1416
01:36:14,380 --> 01:36:20,260
And I believe Colonel John Alexander knew about Rendlesham before just about anybody else in the United States.

1417
01:36:20,260 --> 01:36:21,120
Probably so, yeah.

1418
01:36:21,120 --> 01:36:24,460
Was he involved in your, I guess you can't probably say or.

1419
01:36:24,820 --> 01:36:32,740
No, John was rarely, I don't think he was ever involved in our unit.

1420
01:36:32,820 --> 01:36:33,120
Okay.

1421
01:36:33,120 --> 01:36:41,260
But Bert, Albert Stubblebine, General Stubblebine, became a really good friend.

1422
01:36:41,260 --> 01:36:42,320
And I always called him Bert.

1423
01:36:43,000 --> 01:36:48,960
And Bert intentionally kept him out of it.

1424
01:36:49,460 --> 01:36:56,600
Albert Stubblebine is a very interesting figure who seems very conspiratorial himself.

1425
01:36:56,600 --> 01:36:58,980
He became like a second father to me.

1426
01:36:59,160 --> 01:37:00,760
I just treasure that man.

1427
01:37:01,640 --> 01:37:04,440
What is his, tell us about him.

1428
01:37:04,480 --> 01:37:07,600
Because he's this very intriguing figure in kind of UFO lore.

1429
01:37:07,600 --> 01:37:13,340
Like when Stephen Greer, for example, initially gets into all this stuff.

1430
01:37:13,380 --> 01:37:15,840
He sort of, he was this emergency medical doctor.

1431
01:37:15,840 --> 01:37:19,840
And then he developed CE5, this protocol to sort of call in UFOs.

1432
01:37:20,160 --> 01:37:28,200
And Stubblebine is first on the scene to, you know, ostensibly try to almost recruit him into some sort of government program.

1433
01:37:28,860 --> 01:37:28,920
Yeah.

1434
01:37:29,340 --> 01:37:31,640
So what is, what is Stubblebine like?

1435
01:37:31,640 --> 01:37:32,740
Bert was very interested in it.

1436
01:37:32,740 --> 01:37:41,360
Bert had the project going where he had people out looking for PK events and things like this.

1437
01:37:41,480 --> 01:37:49,200
That's how, that's how I got reported to Bert, who was head of the Intelligence and Security Command.

1438
01:37:49,560 --> 01:37:54,140
That's why he came out to the unit and wanted to talk to me.

1439
01:37:54,880 --> 01:37:59,920
And at that, we've seen the movie, The Man Who Stare at Goats.

1440
01:38:00,120 --> 01:38:00,360
Yeah.

1441
01:38:00,360 --> 01:38:08,760
He shoved me into the office and told the commander, I need to talk to Sergeant Buchanan and get out, you know.

1442
01:38:09,060 --> 01:38:16,000
He turned to me and got up in my face and said, did you kill my computers with your mind?

1443
01:38:17,160 --> 01:38:20,360
And I thought, I have got to lie about this.

1444
01:38:21,460 --> 01:38:22,660
I knew I had.

1445
01:38:22,660 --> 01:38:26,860
And I could see my grandchildren paying for computers.

1446
01:38:27,560 --> 01:38:31,120
You know, basically, I heard myself say, yes, sir, I did.

1447
01:38:31,120 --> 01:38:44,580
And the grin that comes across General Hapgood's face in that movie is exactly the grin that came across Bert's face.

1448
01:38:45,320 --> 01:38:49,360
And you can, you can blip this out if you want.

1449
01:38:50,660 --> 01:38:57,700
Just immediately right there in my face, he said, far fucking out have I ever got a job for you.

1450
01:38:57,700 --> 01:38:59,600
Ah, that's awesome.

1451
01:38:59,840 --> 01:39:00,080
Yeah.

1452
01:39:00,640 --> 01:39:01,080
Wow.

1453
01:39:01,380 --> 01:39:01,560
Yeah.

1454
01:39:02,080 --> 01:39:08,080
Who do you think tasked him initially with assembling this X-Men team of Psychic?

1455
01:39:08,080 --> 01:39:09,620
I think he did it all on his own.

1456
01:39:09,740 --> 01:39:11,480
He got all kinds of flack from that.

1457
01:39:11,840 --> 01:39:12,160
Really?

1458
01:39:12,260 --> 01:39:13,140
He really did.

1459
01:39:13,240 --> 01:39:14,860
So he kind of went rogue a little bit.

1460
01:39:15,020 --> 01:39:15,240
Yeah.

1461
01:39:15,740 --> 01:39:16,040
Hmm.

1462
01:39:16,040 --> 01:39:20,560
Such a fascinating world, you know, all of this stuff.

1463
01:39:20,660 --> 01:39:28,300
And I always, I find it interesting too, because you have Hal Puthoff is one of these guys who's kind of, you know, one of the godfathers of remote viewing.

1464
01:39:28,460 --> 01:39:28,940
He's great.

1465
01:39:29,180 --> 01:39:30,020
Amazing guy.

1466
01:39:30,140 --> 01:39:30,360
Yeah.

1467
01:39:30,680 --> 01:39:34,160
And, but then he also is at the forefront of the UFO stuff.

1468
01:39:34,280 --> 01:39:35,760
And that has to be significant.

1469
01:39:35,760 --> 01:39:37,340
Like, to me, at least.

1470
01:39:37,340 --> 01:39:42,360
I think there has to be this, like, essential overlap between these two things.

1471
01:39:43,980 --> 01:39:44,460
Okay.

1472
01:39:44,840 --> 01:39:44,900
Yeah.

1473
01:39:46,040 --> 01:39:55,860
Um, you've heard a lot of stories that when a person gets abducted, they suddenly start having psychic ability?

1474
01:39:56,460 --> 01:39:56,800
Yes.

1475
01:39:57,200 --> 01:39:57,540
Okay.

1476
01:39:58,200 --> 01:40:04,480
I was tasked to do a paper that, as soon as I turned it in, it disappeared.

1477
01:40:04,480 --> 01:40:15,660
I don't know if it's in that place where, that big warehouse where, at the end of the Indiana Jones movie.

1478
01:40:16,040 --> 01:40:26,480
The task was compare and contrast our psychic ability with the E.T. psychic ability.

1479
01:40:26,480 --> 01:40:35,360
And, um, I got access to a bunch of stuff that most people will never see.

1480
01:40:35,420 --> 01:40:48,000
But, um, the end result of that study that I did, I had already found out that you can divide psychically the E.T.s into four different groups.

1481
01:40:48,000 --> 01:40:57,940
Uh, there's not us and them, there's us and them and them and them and them and them and them and them and them and them and them and you can cut them into four different groups, friends and enemies.

1482
01:40:57,940 --> 01:41:06,600
Um, and those who have more psychic ability than we have and those who are equal or less psychic than we are.

1483
01:41:06,600 --> 01:41:14,260
Um, the enemies who are equal or less than we are try to stay away from here.

1484
01:41:14,260 --> 01:41:16,320
They don't like us, they don't like us, okay?

1485
01:41:17,320 --> 01:41:25,120
The friends who are less or equal to us psychically come here for trade.

1486
01:41:26,180 --> 01:41:27,520
Come here for trade.

1487
01:41:28,400 --> 01:41:37,040
And, um, the ones who are more psychic than we are and friends want us to become psychic.

1488
01:41:37,040 --> 01:41:45,940
The ones who are enemies and more psychic than we are don't want us off this planet.

1489
01:41:46,340 --> 01:41:51,480
They'd be very happy to just wipe the planet off, you know, kill all humans, period.

1490
01:41:52,220 --> 01:41:54,440
And, uh, I couldn't figure out why.

1491
01:41:55,260 --> 01:42:05,340
And this one, um, this one event that I got the record of, there were three guys camping at a lake.

1492
01:42:05,340 --> 01:42:13,940
And they, it was nighttime, they saw a UFO come, and they were standing there on the lake looking at it.

1493
01:42:14,420 --> 01:42:21,060
It came up right over them, and all of a sudden they couldn't move, they were frozen, and they got abducted.

1494
01:42:22,500 --> 01:42:33,720
And there was something about that that, uh, sort of just made everything that I had studied before that fall together.

1495
01:42:33,720 --> 01:42:42,780
And that is that those ETs had much more psychic ability than the humans, but no range.

1496
01:42:43,960 --> 01:42:47,480
They had to be right over them in order to do anything.

1497
01:42:48,200 --> 01:42:57,360
With the remote viewing, we can see across space and time, like looking across the room at a stove or something, you know?

1498
01:42:57,360 --> 01:42:57,960
Mm-hmm.

1499
01:42:57,960 --> 01:42:58,660
No different.

1500
01:42:59,660 --> 01:43:09,760
If we develop our psychic ability, when we get out into space, we are going to be a power in the universe,

1501
01:43:09,820 --> 01:43:16,820
because we can see way into the future, anywhere in space, and all that.

1502
01:43:17,380 --> 01:43:19,380
And evidently they can't.

1503
01:43:19,640 --> 01:43:20,000
Mm-hmm.

1504
01:43:20,000 --> 01:43:22,740
And so we have that ability.

1505
01:43:23,280 --> 01:43:31,240
That's why our friends want us out there, and our enemies don't want us off this planet.

1506
01:43:32,000 --> 01:43:38,960
Do you have a sense of, like, taxonomies of non-human intelligence, like the species and stuff?

1507
01:43:38,960 --> 01:43:47,480
Because I'm not going to lie, when I speak to people about, when people volunteer information about this, I'm often skeptical.

1508
01:43:47,840 --> 01:43:54,800
And then in the event in which we are, you know, being visited by non-human intelligence, which I believe we are.

1509
01:43:54,920 --> 01:43:55,240
Oh, yeah.

1510
01:43:55,420 --> 01:44:01,160
Then it's somehow obviously very important to categorize them, as you just have.

1511
01:44:01,220 --> 01:44:06,180
But can you categorize them further by they're from XYZ planet, you know?

1512
01:44:06,240 --> 01:44:07,840
Oh, you mean in those four groups?

1513
01:44:07,840 --> 01:44:11,700
Yeah, I mean, like, the classic thing would be, like, Nordic greys, reptilians, like—

1514
01:44:11,700 --> 01:44:18,620
What I found was that, like, the Nordics, the greys, and all that fit into all four groups.

1515
01:44:19,000 --> 01:44:19,400
Mm-hmm.

1516
01:44:19,400 --> 01:44:30,680
So there are greys that hate us, greys that like us, greys that are more psychic than we are, greys that couldn't view their way out of a paper bag if the top was open, you know?

1517
01:44:30,680 --> 01:44:31,300
Mm-hmm.

1518
01:44:31,300 --> 01:44:33,660
And like many of us.

1519
01:44:33,660 --> 01:45:01,340
And that there was no—seemed to be no separating them, according to type, into any of those four groups that—at some point, there are people in any of those four groups that—I mean, in any race that fit into all those four groups.

1520
01:45:01,340 --> 01:45:04,960
Have you ever seen a UFO in a hangar?

1521
01:45:05,760 --> 01:45:06,940
Not in a hangar.

1522
01:45:07,500 --> 01:45:15,340
Well, in the viewing of Mount Hayes, Mount Zeal.

1523
01:45:15,340 --> 01:45:20,660
Have you ever seen a UFO in the possession of the American military?

1524
01:45:20,900 --> 01:45:25,420
Not just a UFO that's flying around, you know, in the woods somewhere or something or whatever?

1525
01:45:25,420 --> 01:45:41,220
The only one I've seen was in that hangar where the collision had taken place, and there was just a massive dump of debris, and that control panel was there in that debris.

1526
01:45:41,460 --> 01:45:42,880
And so where was this?

1527
01:45:43,040 --> 01:45:43,920
Where did you see this?

1528
01:45:43,920 --> 01:45:47,740
You're back to where I can't answer.

1529
01:45:48,140 --> 01:45:48,620
Can't answer.

1530
01:45:50,400 --> 01:45:53,980
But so you must have had a very high clearance at the time?

1531
01:45:54,620 --> 01:45:54,940
Oh, yeah.

1532
01:45:55,020 --> 01:46:05,900
I had one of the highest clearances, not only for the remote viewing, but for other stuff that I've done that will never be talked about.

1533
01:46:05,900 --> 01:46:11,740
And I've heard that only 17 people have ever had that.

1534
01:46:12,120 --> 01:46:12,460
Really?

1535
01:46:12,520 --> 01:46:13,980
I don't know if that's true or not.

1536
01:46:14,240 --> 01:46:17,060
So it's basically the highest clearance you can get?

1537
01:46:17,060 --> 01:46:24,800
Oh, when I was given that clearance, he said, that's the highest clearance I've ever given anybody.

1538
01:46:25,480 --> 01:46:27,680
And I said, well, what is the highest clearance?

1539
01:46:28,680 --> 01:46:31,800
He said, oh, there is one, but nobody ever gets it.

1540
01:46:32,160 --> 01:46:33,100
And I said, what's that?

1541
01:46:33,100 --> 01:46:34,500
And he said, truth.

1542
01:46:36,600 --> 01:46:37,000
Truth.

1543
01:46:37,400 --> 01:46:38,160
I like that.

1544
01:46:38,240 --> 01:46:38,560
Truth.

1545
01:46:38,700 --> 01:46:40,020
Nobody learns the truth.

1546
01:46:40,060 --> 01:46:40,780
Yeah, that's funny.

1547
01:46:41,240 --> 01:46:45,500
But you had the highest human clearance in the federal government.

1548
01:46:45,500 --> 01:46:49,420
I just, I had the highest clearance of anybody I've ever met.

1549
01:46:49,740 --> 01:46:49,820
Okay.

1550
01:46:49,920 --> 01:46:55,400
And one time, Bert and I were out at lunch, and he said, what is your clearance?

1551
01:46:55,540 --> 01:47:00,440
And I said, T-S-E-S-I-S-I-O-P.

1552
01:47:01,580 --> 01:47:07,900
And his utensils went down, and he said, what?

1553
01:47:08,240 --> 01:47:10,320
He said, I can't even get that.

1554
01:47:12,460 --> 01:47:12,900
Oh.

1555
01:47:12,900 --> 01:47:21,640
And so, anyway, but it was because of other work that, outside of the remote viewing unit

1556
01:47:21,640 --> 01:47:27,460
and outside of all the other that I was doing.

1557
01:47:28,840 --> 01:47:32,640
Well, I think that clearance needs a little bit of a rebrand for our audience.

1558
01:47:32,760 --> 01:47:35,500
That is not PSYOP psychological operation.

1559
01:47:35,600 --> 01:47:36,120
No, it's not.

1560
01:47:36,460 --> 01:47:40,540
It's Strategic Integrated Operation, S-I-O-P.

1561
01:47:40,600 --> 01:47:41,800
S-I-O-P.

1562
01:47:41,800 --> 01:47:42,240
Yeah.

1563
01:47:42,240 --> 01:47:43,560
So, don't get any ideas.

1564
01:47:43,860 --> 01:47:44,020
No.

1565
01:47:44,020 --> 01:47:50,440
But this UFO that you saw the debris of in a hangar, did you see that in person?

1566
01:47:50,900 --> 01:47:51,100
Yeah.

1567
01:47:51,440 --> 01:47:52,960
So, that wasn't a remote viewing session.

1568
01:47:53,660 --> 01:47:55,140
No, that wasn't a remote view.

1569
01:47:55,140 --> 01:47:56,540
I was standing there in front of it.

1570
01:47:56,880 --> 01:48:00,220
You were standing in front of a crashed UFO in a hangar.

1571
01:48:00,220 --> 01:48:04,760
And this hangar was dealing with mid-air collisions.

1572
01:48:04,760 --> 01:48:12,580
And so, the guy, my friend was showing me around and showing me how they put the planes back together and all that.

1573
01:48:12,820 --> 01:48:19,760
And they had these piles of rubble all over and they were, you know, to figure out what happened with the mid-air collision.

1574
01:48:19,760 --> 01:48:21,280
And we passed by this one.

1575
01:48:21,280 --> 01:48:26,180
And here was the control panel of a UFO, which I had seen and operated before.

1576
01:48:26,180 --> 01:48:31,560
And I said, that's out of UFO.

1577
01:48:31,560 --> 01:48:38,960
And it echoed in this metal Quonset building.

1578
01:48:38,960 --> 01:48:51,600
And immediately, the colonel who was in charge came running out of his office and, I mean, just ran me out of the place.

1579
01:48:52,900 --> 01:48:55,620
A lot of questions.

1580
01:48:56,100 --> 01:48:57,900
So, you said something interesting there.

1581
01:48:57,960 --> 01:49:00,140
You said, which I had operated before.

1582
01:49:00,140 --> 01:49:07,280
So, you knew that this was a UFO control panel because you had some prior experience with it?

1583
01:49:07,280 --> 01:49:12,660
I had a—I was abducted, okay?

1584
01:49:13,580 --> 01:49:19,060
I was a Methodist minister in East Texas.

1585
01:49:19,060 --> 01:49:30,100
And the Methodists used—they moved their young preachers around from church to church to give them experience.

1586
01:49:30,740 --> 01:49:32,780
Every year, you move to a different church.

1587
01:49:33,400 --> 01:49:35,180
And it was time to move.

1588
01:49:35,640 --> 01:49:38,640
My family had already moved to the new parsonage.

1589
01:49:38,920 --> 01:49:40,320
And when you say parsonage—

1590
01:49:40,320 --> 01:49:43,100
Parsonage is where the preacher lives.

1591
01:49:43,260 --> 01:49:44,820
It's the house where the preacher lives.

1592
01:49:44,880 --> 01:49:45,200
Okay.

1593
01:49:45,200 --> 01:49:49,160
I was cleaning out the old parsonage, got it all cleaned out.

1594
01:49:49,260 --> 01:49:50,540
Everything was in the U-Haul.

1595
01:49:51,760 --> 01:49:54,180
And it was late at night.

1596
01:49:55,000 --> 01:49:56,140
And I was tired.

1597
01:49:56,340 --> 01:50:02,520
So, I made a pallet down on the living room floor and laid down.

1598
01:50:03,360 --> 01:50:08,080
And I was wide awake.

1599
01:50:09,440 --> 01:50:11,740
And I heard something laying in the backyard.

1600
01:50:11,740 --> 01:50:15,940
Now, this was a country church.

1601
01:50:16,640 --> 01:50:23,480
We were over a quarter mile off the nearest road in the woods and all that.

1602
01:50:24,020 --> 01:50:28,000
And I heard something land in the backyard.

1603
01:50:29,240 --> 01:50:31,560
And I knew it wasn't a helicopter.

1604
01:50:32,700 --> 01:50:34,300
It didn't sound like a helicopter.

1605
01:50:34,300 --> 01:50:50,980
It sounded like—the best example I can give is where some kid sticks a playing card into the spokes of his bicycle and, you know, it was like that.

1606
01:50:51,880 --> 01:50:59,100
And so, I was going to get up and go to the back room and see what was in the backyard.

1607
01:50:59,500 --> 01:51:00,740
I couldn't move.

1608
01:51:00,980 --> 01:51:02,140
And I was wide awake.

1609
01:51:02,240 --> 01:51:04,020
It wasn't sleep paralysis at all.

1610
01:51:04,020 --> 01:51:05,000
I was wide awake.

1611
01:51:05,440 --> 01:51:06,580
I couldn't move.

1612
01:51:07,300 --> 01:51:13,420
And I heard somebody walking around the house to the front window looking in.

1613
01:51:15,320 --> 01:51:17,820
And immediately, I woke up.

1614
01:51:18,520 --> 01:51:21,320
And I was sitting in a white room.

1615
01:51:22,360 --> 01:51:23,980
There were two rows of seats.

1616
01:51:23,980 --> 01:51:27,700
And I was sitting here.

1617
01:51:28,340 --> 01:51:32,280
There was an elderly, elderly woman sitting here.

1618
01:51:32,760 --> 01:51:35,160
I tried talking to her, and she was just frozen.

1619
01:51:35,940 --> 01:51:38,080
And there were empty seats over here in the window.

1620
01:51:38,080 --> 01:51:43,880
Now, when I fly, I have to have a window seat.

1621
01:51:44,520 --> 01:51:47,660
I can't deal with being inside.

1622
01:51:48,020 --> 01:51:49,840
You know, I have to have a window seat.

1623
01:51:49,900 --> 01:51:50,840
Especially on a UFO.

1624
01:51:50,840 --> 01:51:53,260
Well, no, in a plane.

1625
01:51:53,260 --> 01:52:12,920
And so, I was sitting there, and this tall, muscled up, must have been seven feet tall, and muscled up like Arnold Schwarzenegger, and just pale as could be, came into the room there.

1626
01:52:12,920 --> 01:52:18,000
And I said, excuse me, can I sit by the window?

1627
01:52:18,260 --> 01:52:22,580
He got this look of fear on his face and turned around and ran out.

1628
01:52:22,580 --> 01:52:35,900
And so, a few minutes later, a little gray with three of these big guys huddled behind the gray for protection, you know, came in.

1629
01:52:36,080 --> 01:52:41,280
And the gray started talking to me, and I would nod, almost going to sleep, and wake up.

1630
01:52:42,020 --> 01:52:45,880
Finally, the gray said, you know, we've got work to do.

1631
01:52:46,360 --> 01:52:47,080
Come with me.

1632
01:52:47,700 --> 01:52:49,080
He took me up front.

1633
01:52:49,200 --> 01:52:50,080
He was the pilot.

1634
01:52:50,080 --> 01:52:56,100
And he had me kneel down in front of the control panel.

1635
01:52:57,200 --> 01:53:02,280
With me kneeling down and him standing, we were eye to eye.

1636
01:53:03,080 --> 01:53:05,640
So, that tells you his size, you know.

1637
01:53:06,200 --> 01:53:08,660
But I was watching him.

1638
01:53:09,020 --> 01:53:09,900
He was talking.

1639
01:53:10,020 --> 01:53:11,780
We were talking to each other and all that.

1640
01:53:12,140 --> 01:53:13,580
